\# Code Review: KAN-6 Python FastAPI Base Application



\## Summary



This PR implements KAN-6, delivering a production-ready Python FastAPI application template for OpenSpec backend projects. The implementation includes a complete Clean Architecture / Domain-Driven Design stack with async SQLAlchemy, Alembic migrations, Pydantic validation, comprehensive tests, and CI/CD setup. The architecture is well-structured with clear separation of concerns across domain, application, presentation, and infrastructure layers. \*\*However, there is a critical security issue and several test gaps that must be addressed before approval.\*\*



\*\*Verdict: REQUEST CHANGES\*\* (blocker: committed credentials)



\---



\## Architecture \& Design



✅ \*\*Strong DDD Layered Architecture\*\*

\- \*\*Domain Layer\*\* (health.py, health\_repository.py, health\_exceptions.py): Pure Python dataclasses, factory methods enforce invariants, repository interfaces decouple from persistence.

\- \*\*Application Layer\*\* (health\_service.py): Service uses constructor injection of repository interface, accepts validated DTOs, raises domain exceptions.

\- \*\*Presentation Layer\*\* (health\_router.py, global\_handlers.py): Thin routers, centralized exception handling, proper HTTP status codes (201 create, 204 delete, 422 validation, 404 not found).

\- \*\*Infrastructure Layer\*\* (health\_repository\_impl.py, engine.py, health\_orm.py): ORM models isolated, async session factory, proper async/await usage.



✅ \*\*Proper Separation of Concerns\*\*: No framework imports in domain/application; SQLAlchemy restricted to infrastructure.



✅ \*\*Dependency Injection\*\*: FastAPI `Depends()` properly wired; constructor injection throughout.



\---



\## Code Quality



✅ \*\*Type Hints\*\*: All functions explicitly typed; `from \_\_future\_\_ import annotations` for forward references.



✅ \*\*Naming Conventions\*\*: PascalCase classes, snake\_case functions/variables, snake\_case database tables all followed.



✅ \*\*Exception Hierarchy\*\*: Domain exceptions with proper HTTP status codes (400, 404, 409, 422, 500) mapped correctly.



⚠️ \*\*Enum Handling\*\*: health.py uses string enum with values `"healthy"`, `"degraded"`, `"unhealthy"`. Mapping between Pydantic validation, domain model, and ORM storage works but needs careful testing.



\---



\## Testing



✅ \*\*Unit Tests\*\* (test\_health\_service.py):

\- AAA pattern followed

\- Happy path tested

\- Validation errors tested (blank service\_name, blank version, negative uptime)

\- Mocking properly used with `AsyncMock`



⚠️ \*\*Integration Tests\*\* (test\_health\_endpoints.py):

\- 201 (create), 200 (list), 422 (validation) tested ✓

\- \*\*Missing: explicit 404 test when health record not found\*\* — the `test\_should\_return\_422\_for\_invalid\_health\_request` only tests validation; no test for `GET /health/{non-existent-id}`



⚠️ \*\*E2E Tests\*\* (test\_full\_health\_flow.py):

\- Full CRUD flow tested

\- But only one test case — not comprehensive for edge cases



⚠️ \*\*Coverage Threshold\*\*: Code appears to cover \~70-80% of paths, but \*\*90% is required\*\*. Missing test cases:

\- 404 not found on GET by ID

\- 404 not found on UPDATE

\- DELETE on non-existent record behavior

\- Edge cases for HealthStatus enum

\- Concurrent request handling



\*\*Fixture Issue\*\* (conftest.py):

```python

async def get\_test\_session() -> AsyncSession:

&#x20;   async with AsyncSessionFactory() as test\_session:

&#x20;       yield test\_session

```

This returns an async generator, but the dependency override should properly await it. FastAPI's dependency system might not handle this correctly. \*\*This needs testing to confirm it works.\*\*



