\## Security



🚨 \*\*CRITICAL: Committed .env File with Credentials\*\*



The .env file is committed to the repository with actual credentials:

```

JIRA\_TOKEN=ATATT3xFfGF0HKQKKdOF\_sdiPiL8Y3qvzfBolnz3-\_E8NMTHfCn3Q9LHURzDYpiQ3gCwiXdyZotfiqNKEKuOQCZfLIVQRzOXGu6ESBr9rTv2IBYl7dNARYqzcd\_JVjWNl3LoD2sHD4GIVmJMa5xd16kbwxXnspGzcLP9SpUu1Utpl6b\_aWg1c-0=2A546FCB

JIRA\_EMAIL=ingjohnaragon@gmail.com

```



\*\*This is a major security vulnerability.\*\* The .env file should:

\- Be added to .gitignore

\- Be removed from git history (use `git filter-branch` or `git-filter-repo`)

\- The JIRA token should be rotated immediately

\- A .env.example template exists but the actual file was still committed



✅ \*\*Other Security\*\*: 

\- No hardcoded secrets in code ✓

\- Environment variables used correctly for database URL ✓

\- Input validation via Pydantic ✓

\- No sensitive data in logs ✓



