\## Specific Issues



| File | Line | Severity | Issue | Fix |

|------|------|----------|-------|-----|

| .env | — | \*\*CRITICAL\*\* | Credentials committed to repo (JIRA\_TOKEN visible) | Remove .env, add to .gitignore, rotate JIRA token immediately, clean git history |

| test\_health\_endpoints.py | — | \*\*MAJOR\*\* | Missing test for 404 when GET by ID not found | Add test: `test\_should\_return\_404\_when\_health\_id\_not\_found()` |

| test\_health\_endpoints.py | — | \*\*MAJOR\*\* | Missing test for UPDATE on non-existent record | Add test: `test\_should\_return\_404\_when\_updating\_nonexistent\_health()` |

| conftest.py | 28-32 | \*\*MAJOR\*\* | Async session fixture may not work with FastAPI dependency injection | Verify the fixture is properly awaited; consider using `lifespan` context manager or `AsyncTestClient` |

| health\_repository\_impl.py | 50-54 | \*\*MINOR\*\* | `delete\_by\_id` silently succeeds if record not found | Consider raising `HealthNotFoundError` or returning a status; document current behavior |

| env.py | 9 | \*\*MINOR\*\* | `sys.path.append(BASE\_DIR)` may fail if called from different directory | Use `sys.path.insert(0, os.path.dirname(...)` or rely on package installation |

| pyproject.toml | 27 | \*\*MINOR\*\* | Test dependencies in optional, but conftest imports them unconditionally | Move test dependencies to main or ensure they're installed for dev |



